        <updateDate>2022-01-14T13:27:37Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Open Schools Responsibly Act</b></p> <p>This bill limits civil liability for elementary and secondary schools and institutions of higher education relating to any harm arising from exposure to, or infection by, COVID-19 suffered by a student, employee, or visitor. Specifically, a school or institution shall not be liable for such harm if the school or institution was in compliance with applicable state requirements. However, a school or institution may be liable for acts or omissions that constitute willful or criminal misconduct, gross negligence, reckless misconduct, or a conscious flagrant indifference to the rights or safety of the individual harmed. <br /></p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
